---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Quick Start">
  <h1>Quick Start</h1>

  <p>Create your first agent in under 5 minutes.</p>

  <h2>1. Create an Agent</h2>
  <pre><code>agent-forge create "review PRs for logic errors and style violations"</code></pre>
  <p>The CLI will prompt for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Output target</strong> — Claude Skills or Standalone</li>
    <li><strong>Tools</strong> — comma-separated list (default: read_file, run_command)</li>
    <li><strong>Pass threshold</strong> — 0.0 to 1.0 (default: 0.85)</li>
    <li><strong>Max iterations</strong> — refinement loop limit (default: 5)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Watch the Loop Run</h2>
  <pre><code>[1/5] Generating agent...
[2/5] Evaluating...
[2/5] Score: 0.62 - refining...
[3/5] Refining agent (attempt 3)...
[3/5] Evaluating...
[3/5] Score: 0.71 - refining...
[4/5] Refining agent (attempt 4)...
[4/5] Evaluating...
[4/5] Score: 0.88 - agent passed quality gate</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Inspect the Result</h2>
  <pre><code># List all agents
agent-forge list

# Inspect version history
agent-forge history pr_reviewer

# Inspect specific version
agent-forge inspect pr_reviewer --v 3</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Use the Agent</h2>
  <p>If exported to Claude Skills, the agent is available at <code>~/.claude/skills/pr_reviewer/</code>.</p>
  <p>If exported as standalone:</p>
  <pre><code>cd agents/pr_reviewer
bun run agent.ts sample input here</code></pre>

  <h2>Programmatic Usage</h2>
  <pre><code>import runLoop from "agent-forge/runloop";

const result = await runLoop(&lcub;
  description: "review PRs for logic errors",
  name: "pr_reviewer",
  tools: ["gh_api", "read_file"],
  threshold: 0.85,
  maxIterations: 5,
  outputMode: "claude-skills",
&rcub;);

if (result.passed) &lcub;
  console.log("Agent created at: " + result.path);
&rcub; else &lcub;
  console.log("Best score: " + result.bestScore);
&rcub;</code></pre>

  <h2>What Happens Inside the Loop</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Generate</strong> — LLM produces a TypeScript agent file from NL description</li>
    <li><strong>Test Generation</strong> — LLM creates k=5 diverse test cases traced to intent clauses</li>
    <li><strong>Evaluate</strong> — Agent runs against each test; LLM judge scores semantic quality</li>
    <li><strong>Quality Gate</strong> — Composite score (60% tests + 40% judge) checked against threshold</li>
    <li><strong>Refine</strong> — If gate fails, LLM refiner rewrites targeted parts of the agent</li>
    <li><strong>Repeat</strong> — Loop until pass or max iterations reached</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="tip">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> Start with a narrow, specific task. "Review PRs for logic errors" works better than "be a code expert."
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .tip {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-warning);
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    padding: 0.875rem 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .tip strong {
    color: var(--color-warning);
  }
</style>
